This paper deals with the problem of community detection in networks, which is a common topic in several subfields of computer science. The use of modularity functions and eigenvectors suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and computational methods, which could place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. The paper also discusses the application of the method to real-world datasets, which could suggest the cs.SD (Software Engineering) category. Finally, the paper involves network analysis, which could place it in the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) category.
